WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:08.000
Okay, in terms of calls, generally when I need pricing urgently, I'll call the relevant supplier for the equipment.

00:08.000 --> 00:16.000
As this generates the pricing or costing verbally via the call, it works out a lot faster in that route.

00:16.000 --> 00:24.000
If it's not urgent, I generally email and then we follow up later on during the course of the day or the very next day.

00:24.000 --> 00:34.000
So top three suppliers for valves, we're looking at valve specialist, MAC, Fluid, also EMV Africa.

00:34.000 --> 00:44.000
And in this context too, it all depends what sort of valve, because each supplier has different unique suppliers of valves for themselves.

00:44.000 --> 00:54.000
Also for the hydraulics, I look at mainly one supplier, hydro systems, as they generally are very knowledgeable and they give me one of the best prices.

00:54.000 --> 01:02.000
But also in the same context, they don't do hydraulic filtration systems, they don't do hydraulic quick couplers.

01:02.000 --> 01:07.000
So this I have to get from a different supplier, which is hydro sales.

01:07.000 --> 01:17.000
Suppliers I wish I had, obviously this generally comes up only when it's equipment that I haven't dealt with.

01:17.000 --> 01:26.000
Most of the equipment I deal with is all familiar to me, so I don't think I have any supplies I would want to put on as yet.

